=== Detailed Description ===
In our RHEV installation we are going to have a lot of VLAN's in a
cluster. This means that when adding a host to this cluster, it means a
lot of work adding all the different networks. Also, when adding a VLAN,
it means a lot of work adding the VLAN to all the hosts.

It would be a good feature to be able to have a host profile, where you
have:
NIC A
NIC B
NIC C

On host1 you then specify for instance:
eth0 = NIC A
eth1 = NIC C
eth2 = NIC B
And on host2:
bond0 = NIC A
eth0 = NIC B
eth1 = NIC C

And then you assign a VLAN to for example NIC A, and all hosts in the
cluster will have that VLAN assigned to the right NIC, without having to
add it to all the hosts in the cluster
